Now we have the existence of a quaternion algebra $D/F$ and an automorphic eigenform $\pi$ for level $S$.

To construct the automorphic form for $\rho|_E$, we need to base change $\pi$ from $F$ to $E$. Since $E/F$ is solvable, the base change will be an automorphic form for $D_E := D \otimes_F E$ over $E$.

The level $U_1(S_E)$ will be the preimage of $U_1(S)$ under the natural map $\text{GL}_2(E) \to \text{GL}_2(F)$.

The associated Galois representation will be $\rho|_E$.

